key_points: The discovery of Gabby Petito's body has renewed interest in the case of missing man Daniel Robinson.
Daniel Robinson, a geologist, went missing after leaving a job site in the Arizona desert on June 23.
Robinson's last known location was near Sun Valley Parkway and Cactus Road, driving a 2017 blue Jeep Renegade.
Robinson is missing his right forearm and hand, described as 5-foot-8 with black hair and brown eyes.
His damaged vehicle was found on July 19 near a ravine, with personal items inside, but no sign of Daniel.
A human skull found on July 31 was not identified as Daniel's; foul play is not suspected by investigators.
Daniel's father, David Robinson II, has initiated a GoFundMe for a private investigation and search efforts, raising over $34,000.
Private investigator Jeff McGrath discovered the Jeep was driven 11 miles post-crash, with several attempts to restart the engine.
An online petition calls for further investigation by police, amassing over 5,700 signatures.
Buckeye Police Department states they have thoroughly searched and analyzed evidence but found no new leads on Daniel's whereabouts.
spokespersons: David Robinson II (Father of the missing man)
